      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "cyclic -  - Adapts the range of the Lookup Table (2nd input) for cyclic or non-cyclic input indices. When using a cyclic input index (1st input), the lookup value for index 0.0 and 1.0 result in the same value. To avoid this, set Cyclic Range to Yes and the lookup will cycle smoothly.\n\n auto - Checks the right extend condition of each channel (Assumes type cycle and mirror are cyclic lookups). yes - For looking up a cyclic output (oscillator, beat driven output etc). no - For looking up a single wave (slider mapping, etc).",
